# Seeds for failure cases proptest has generated in the past. It is
# automatically read and these particular cases re-run before any
# novel cases are generated.
#
# It is recommended to check this file in to source control so that
# everyone who runs the test benefits from these saved cases.
#
# Seeds cleared when the `b64_secret_with_internal_plus_surfaces` generator was
# corrected to draw bodies from BASE62_ALPHABET (strategy range 0u8..62u8). The
# prior seeds were failures of the OLD 64-char base64 generator: a random `/`
# from the body could combine with the inserted `+` to form a uniform-random
# both-punct base64 blob, which the byte-distribution random-blob gate
# DELIBERATELY suppresses (protobuf-of-random-bytes decoys are bench negatives).
# Those were unsound positives, not real regressions, so the seeds are dropped
# rather than carried forward against the corrected generator.
